<method name="firedOnWidget"  public="true">
<description>
The Niagara AX framework calls this method whenever a topic is fired on a user-interface&#xa; widget.  &#xa; &#xa; This method checks if the the event is a user-interface request to pan, tilt, and/or&#xa; zoom a video camera. If so, then this invokes the corresponding &#x27;move&#x27; or &#x27;zoom&#x27;&#xa; action on the station-side component to which this binding glues the client-side&#xa; widget.
</description>
